<Resp>None< /Resp>< Text>
This is among the best vegan fast food we've ever had! We ordered the "Fight the Power" "fried chicken" sandwich and chicken tenders. They are DELICIOUS, perfectly spicy and saucy and will definitely satisfy any fast food craving. Two additional details I appreciated: even though we were about 15 min late in picking up our order, the "chicken" was still crispy by the time we ate it. Also I love how their to-go orders are in boxes - this guarantees that there is no spilling! I highly recommend - we will for sure be coming back! Bonus: they have curly fries!< /Text>

< Review>
This right here is the real deal. Don't get fooled by any other vegan burger option, those other guys might be good but they not this. These guys came from humble beginnings to the best vegan burger spot in Oakland, hands down. Several burger variations plus chickn sandwiches one time for the mind. Milkshakes make you wanna rob a bank. I would recommend this place to all, even those who do not regularly eat vegan food.<//Review>

If it‚Äôs within your budget, I highly recommend it - I‚Äôm not even vegan or vegetarian but I would go back to eat this. 0x80857dab90a4687b:0x621e93d444c0843</gmapID>
< text>
We tried this place the first time because we saw a long line out the door and thought we should give it a try.

Please note, first thing you need to know when you come here is that you're not eating meat. So if you plan to come in here, be open to a slightly different taste. I've eaten plantbased before and totally expect that i am not eating meat. Cost of each entree is on the pricier side, but i recognize that plant-based products are costly, so i respect the price.

We tried the two sandwiches below and it came in a little box. i loved that packaging concept:

GILLIE PHILLY CHEESE STEAK (Like a philly cheesesteak)
LA LULU (Like a Chicken burger)
Side of Fries
Cookies and Cream Milkshake

10/10 The fries are PERFECTLY seasoned and crispy. I like standard fries, with nothing extra on it, so i didnt try it with cheese. However, if you like that, then you may like it with the fries.

9/10 Milkshake, it's good, i would order it again. It's not as creamy as real milk, but again, i knew that so it's great for plantbased.

9/10 My husband had the La LULU, he would order it again. The chicken was crispy, flavorful, and filling. He loved how it tasted like a fried chicken without the oil.

8/10 I had the Gillie. It's a little sweet ( i think from the grilled onions) which surprised me. It wasn't a negative at all, i think some would like it. I truly appreciate an "alternative" philly if i don't want to eat "meat".

The people were lovely inside, friendly and down to earth. I would definitely come again.</text>
</record>

I have tried all of the garden/hydro stores in the Yuba-Sutter area and this place is the best.  The prices are fair and the product selection is great. <rate>5<//rate><Text>Not a strenuous hiking trail but it's long enough and has a good enough incline to make for a solid round-trip workout. Plan on 1.5 hrs roundtrip with time to stop to take pics. Roundtrip distance is about 4.7 miles from the gate on GMR to the Mystic Cayon upper marker with the flag, and back. The trail continues even further up around the back of the Punk Out peak though (that round trip hike is about 7.7 miles) Beautiful views. Take a flashlight if you are out near sunset, the canyon gets dark fast. Watch for mountainbikers... It's a single track route and they love it too!</Text>< user_name>
Amanda Valenzuela<//user_name>
